A unique "electronic goods ticket" for return goods Setouchi City added with hometown tax: Sanyo Newspaper Digital|San Digi
"E Street Gift."
i'll contact the dedicated equipment and settle it.
Setonai City announced on July 27 that it would add its own e-machi Gift to the home tax return.
It is available at member stores in the city from November.
It was the first municipality in the prefecture.
If you pay Furusato tax and choose an electronic ticket as a return item, 30% of the donation amount will be sent to the designated smartphone.
At the time of purchase, it shows the screen of the product ticket, and the shop side pays by contacting the stamp-type dedicated equipment.
They cannot be sold or sold.
Recipients usually require a certain amount of time from application to arrival, but electronic goods tickets can be received instantly.
Tourists can use it easily.
In addition to the five Hometown Tax Portals, it is also accepted on two special sites in the city.
The company currently has 13 member stores, with a target of 100 by the end of this fiscal year.
In June, the Ministry of Internal Affairs and Communications (MIC) established a new system to regulate local products in order to prevent excessive competition among municipalities, with the amount of return goods raised to less than 30% of the donation amount.
The city has stated that "it is planned to be a member of a local product company and within the guidelines."
In the 18th year of Setouchi City, the hometown tax amount is about 430 million yen.
