Driving in high heels is dangerous!
Accidents involving the wrong pedal of young people - Yahoo! News
Violations against Road Traffic Law
The number of reports on accidents caused by errors such as pedal treading is increasing, and it is a big mistake to think that this is a problem only for elderly drivers.
According to the 2015 National Police Agency data, more than 1080 people aged 24 or younger were killed, surpassing 1032 people aged 75 or older.
It is important to call attention to young people as well.
do you want to take your feet?
is it safe?
There is no description of the gender ratio or cause of this data, but unlike the elderly who are often thought to come from the decline of the body, such as driving skills and reflexes, in the younger generation, it is possible to mistake inadvertently due to other things such as music and conversation, and trampling due to clothes etc.
In particular, women choose a variety of shoes depending on the clothes of the day, such as high heels, pumps, sandals, mules, and others drive as they are.
Although some people know that it is not suitable for driving, it is troublesome to change clothes, some people do not think about the possibility that it will lead to danger at all, and many people drive without evil.
However, driving in high heels and sandals violates the Road Traffic Law.
The first is to ensure that the steering wheel, brakes, and other operations are operated. Article 70 of the Act stipulates that the operation should not be carried out to cause accidents and harm to people.
The other is Article 71, which stipulates that drivers must comply with the matters stipulated by the Public Safety Commission of each prefecture.For example, in Article 12 of the Miyazaki Prefectural Road Traffic Law Enforcement Regulations, there is a sentence that "Do not drive vehicles (except light vehicles) by wearing shoes in a manner that prevents driving operations, or by wearing shoes that may interfere with driving operations."
Even if it is not specified as a high heel, the purpose of each prefecture is similar to that of being considered as a violation of driving in " footwear that may interfere with driving operation."
So why is driving at high heels dangerous?
It is obvious considering the basics of safely pedaling.
For safe pedal operation, first put the foot to be perpendicular to the brake pedal, and when stepping on the accelerator pedal, tilt the foot to the right as a starting point.
At this time, regardless of the behavior of the car, it is important to keep it firmly fixed so that it does not blur.
However, in high heels, the area where the heel is grounded on the floor is small, and it always blurs out as a gravure, and because the height of the heel has an angle throughout the foot, the area of the foot that is grounded on the pedal is smaller and it is difficult to make fine adjustments that can not be firmly trampled.
This may lead to danger.
In addition, most cars have floor carpets, but this material is easy to pull high heels, and when it comes to sudden braking, the heels are pulled and the pedals are not trampled, or the high heels are removed in the time signature that the heels are pulled, and the pedals are stuck in the back of the pedals.
In addition, there is a case where the heel pulls to the back of the pedal when stepping back after stepping on the pedal, and the accelerator pedal disappears.
Toyota and Subaru Accelerate joint development (response) - Yahoo!News
Toyota and Subaru agreed to a new business capital alliance on September 27.
Toyota will acquire additional Subaru shares and become an affiliate of the equity method.
Since the agreement was reached in a business tie-up in 2005, the two companies have been working together to produce Toyota vehicles entrusted by Subaru, supply Toyota vehicles to Subaru, and joint development of the FR sports car "86."
In June of this year, we agreed to develop EV-specific platforms and EV vehicles using Subaru's All-wheel drive technology and Toyota's electrification technology.
In this agreement, Toyota will acquire additional Subaru shares.
At present, Toyota's shareholding in Subaru is 16.83% of the voting rights.
The company is a subsidiary of Toyota.
Meanwhile, Subaru will acquire Toyota shares equivalent to the same amount (up to 8 billion yen) as the amount required for the acquisition of Subaru shares.
Both companies develop and strengthen cooperation through business capital alliances.
We will jointly develop the AWD and 86/BRZ models, expand the installation of THS (Toyota Hybrid System) in Subaru vehicles, coordinate in the connected area, and technological cooperation in the autonomous driving field.
U.S., at least 18,000 people in three consecutive years | Shizuoka Shimbun
The U.S. Department of State announced on October 26, that it will reduce the number of refugees accepted from around the world to 18,000 in the fiscal year 2020 (October 19-20).
The minimum number of refugees since 1980 has been renewed for three consecutive years.
The Trump administration aims to appeal strict immigration and refugee policies to the conservatives in the presidential election next year.
It is inevitable that criticisms from human rights organizations will be made in the midst of the constant number of people being driven out of the country in various places.
The pre-Obama administration set the maximum limit for fiscal 2017 to 110,000, but the Trump administration, which was inaugurated in January 2017, overturned it and reduced it to 50,000.
It has been reduced to 45,000 in FY18 and 30,000 in FY19.
