Katsuyama City, Fukui Prefecture, announced on September 25 that it will acquire approximately 25,000 square meters of land adjacent to the construction site of the road station "Dinosaur Valley Katsuyama," which will open next spring.
In order to accelerate the "industrialization of tourism" advocated by the city and the local economy, we aim to attract accommodation-specific hotels and restaurants.
On the same day, the Board of Directors explained at the Special Committee for the Improvement of Invited Facilities in the City Council.
In addition to the opening of the Hokuriku Shinkansen in the spring of 2023, the entire section of the Chubu Centrair Expressway will be opened, and the prefectural Dinosaur Museum (Katsuyama City) will be expanded and renovated.
It is a private idle land next to the road station construction site east to get.
Surrounded by the Kuzuryu River, Takinami River, and prefectural roads, it is more than twice the size of a roadside station (about 12,000 square meters).
In the name of the industrial complex, the City Land Development Corporation will proceed with land negotiations from this fiscal year and build land in FY21 through land acquisition.
According to the city, private businesses such as farmers' restaurants and harvesting facilities, fast food, and restaurants have already begun to expand their businesses.
