BITPoint, which leaked 3 billion yen worth of crypto assets, to resume service (Genfusha Gold Online) - Yahoo!
In July of this year, crypto asset exchanges, which amounted to 3 billion yen such as Bitcoin, leaked illegally.
Bitpoint Japan Co., Ltd., the operator, announced on September 30 that it would resume the service of sending crypto assets (remittance).
There seems to be a certain point of view, including measures to prevent recurrence.
BITPoint leaked Bitcoin and Ripple this July.
Bitpoint Japan Co., Ltd., which operates the Crypto Asset Exchange BITPoint, announced on September 27 that it will resume the service of sending crypto assets (remittance) at around 14:00 on September 30.
In addition to dealing with customers who suffered damage and exchanging with the Financial Services Agency, there seems to be a certain point of view, including measures to prevent recurrence, such as management management system including security.
Bitpoint Japan says, "We will resume our services as soon as possible, with safety as the first priority, and strive to recover the trust of users."
In July of this year, a cryptocurrency asset fraud incident worth 3 billion yen, including Bitcoin and Ripple, occurred at the exchange.
In the subsequent press conference, regarding the continuation of the business, "There is a current account balance of about 3 billion yen even if the compensation is deducted" "We aim to resume the service as soon as possible based on the priority of user protection."
This article was released on September 27, 2019.
