One year after the earthquake in eastern Iburi Province, water is secured even during power outage.
In response to the total blackout (blackout) caused by the Iburi Eastern Earthquake in September last year, measures are being taken in the condominiums in Hakodate City where the water cut off.
According to the city's Bureau of Water and Sewerage, seven condominiums were installed in one year after the earthquake, and "watering plugs" were installed that could produce water even after the power outage.
There are about 400 condominiums and private housing units in the city that supply water with a "passenger tank type" that can be cut off when a power outage occurs.
The house's water supply system is broadly divided into two types: the "passenger tank type" that once feeds water into the receiving tank located underground or on the roof, and the "direct connection type" that directly feeds each door from the city's water distribution pipe.
Even if the water pipe is not damaged, electric pumps that pump water from the water tank to each door will not be able to run due to power failure, and each door will be cut off.
Training (Aomori Broadcasting) - Yahoo!News
A training session was held in Shingo Village to search and rescue people who had suffered before the autumn mushroom harvest season.
60 people from the police, fire and hunting party participated in the training held at Hirakozawa Forest Park in Shingo Village.
At the opening ceremony, Mr. Tsukeda, Chief of the Goto Police Department, called for close cooperation and training.
★ Takahashi Regional Manager's declaration "We will start mountain training rescue training more than this."
The training was based on the assumption that a man who went out to see the mushroom harvest would not return home at night.
The participants are divided into three groups and search through the mountains with the names of missing men.
In Shingo Village, a 70-year-old man who entered the mountain in June to pick wild vegetables disappeared and was rescued the next day with injuries.
During the training, I found a man who was injured and checked the cooperation from searching to rescue, and prepared for the autumn mushroom harvesting season, which is prone to distress.
