[Yokoyama Wakamizu] There is a circle of children's cafeterias that offer free or inexpensive meals for children nationwide.
According to a survey conducted by NPOs and other organizations, about 3,700 locations nationwide are active this year.
The number increased by one to six times compared to 2018, and there were 24 locations in Fukui Prefecture, which increased by nine compared to last year.
why is it now?
Makoto Yuasa, the chairman and social activist of the Kyoto NPO, spoke about the background and significance at a lecture held in Sakai City.
Due to the declining birthrate and aging population, the area became lonely and the shopping district declined.
There was no place for people to meet.
And he said, "We needed a place where people could interact with each other.
It is a place of multi-generational exchange where elderly people also participate.
It will not only eliminate eating alone, but also help raise children and improve the health of the elderly.
They cut off the chain of poverty and revitalize the region.
the important thing is, don't create children from there.
There are various places to offer meals every day from January 1.
There are a wide variety of venues, from several people to hundreds, from private homes to temples.
The atmosphere is getting ready for people who want to do it.
The low threshold is attractive.
However, it is difficult to secure management and staff.
sometimes we hear about issues like a secure management system
Even though it is said that " values change by engaging with many people" "Connecting with society becomes a safety net in case of disasters," Yuasa said.
It is like the light of hope in a closed society.
