Nike will release eight new models of Air Force 1 (AIR FORCE 1) that have been popular as sneakers representative of the brand since its launch in October 1982.
Three of the eight models are for women, and as Nike Women's Footwear Senior Creative Director Georgena James says, "Women are diverse and seek unique things that are different from others," an update has been added based on her experience in the collection "The One Reimagined" (released in 2018) that redesigns sneakers from a female perspective.
[Image] New 8 models of "Air Force 1" including NBA collaboration and models equipped with "Goretex" appeared at once
The Air Force 1 NBA Pack, which collaborated with the NBA, appeared in two types: low-cut and high-cut.
The low-cut is based on NBA colors such as red, yellow, black, and navy, and the high-cut is available in three teams, including the Los Angeles Lakers.
In addition to the NBA logo on heels and shoetans, satin fabric is used in the back of the upper, and swish is the first by-color design.
The price was 12,200 yen including tax, and it was released on October 1.
The "Air Force 1 Swish Pack" is designed everywhere with the letters and logos of Swish as it is.
It is noteworthy that the part of the shoe tongue, which should originally have a brand logo, has been changed to the character of the special "SWOOSH."
The "Air Force 1 Shadow" is inspired by the shadow and features the side wash and each detail double like a shadow.
The outsole is thicker and taller than the original, while the hollowing out of the center has succeeded in making it lighter for women.
The price was 13,200 yen including tax, and it was released on October 3.
