The Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare (MHLW) announced for the first time on September 26, 424 hospitals in 1455 public hospitals and public hospitals in Japan, including Japan and the Red Cross, which judged that their medical records were poor.
In Fukui Prefecture, the Ministry of Health, Labor, and Welfare examined the treatment results of 14 public and public hospitals, and four facilities were targeted: Awara Hospital, the National Hospital Organization of straw City, Game Sakai City Three Kingdom Hospital, Game Oda Hospital in Echizen Town, Game Wakasa Takahama Hospital in Takahama Town.
⇒4 hospitals subject to reorganization "Standard Funny"
In order to prevent medical expenses from expanding due to an aging population, it was necessary to promote reorganization and integration with hospitals in competing areas.
In October, we will request a full-scale review of reorganization and integration at the target hospital, and we will conclude by September next year.
Although there is no compulsion force, it is expected that local chiefs and residents will be repulsed due to anxiety that hospitals nearby will disappear.
It was announced at the meeting on the same day.
The total number of hospitals targeted was 29.1%, with relatively few beds.
By prefecture, Niigata (53.7%), Hokkaido (48.6%), Miyagi (47.5%), Yamaguchi (46.7%), and Okayama (43.3%).
The number of targets was 54 in Hokkaido, and Okinawa was the only zero.
Based on data from FY2017, the Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare investigated 1455 hospitals in public and public hospitals that can respond to "advanced acute phase" for severe patients and "acute phase" for general surgery.
He analyzed nine medical records, including cancer and emergency medicine, as well as whether competing hospitals were located within 20 minutes by car.
The hospital will be considered to be abolished and some departments will be transferred to other hospitals.
Medical expenses increased rapidly in 25 years, when all baby boomers were 75 or older.
For this reason, the Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare has set a goal of reducing the number of beds in hospitals with 1,246 thousand beds (18 years) to 1191,000 beds nationwide.
Currently, there are many beds in the "altitude acute phase" and "acute phase" where nurses are well placed and medical expenses are taken, but there is a shortage of rehabilitation services that are highly needed for the elderly.
In order to cope with the aging population, it is necessary not only to reduce the number of beds, but also to increase rehabilitation.
For the reorganization and integration of hospitals, each prefecture formulated a "regional medical concept" that defined the number of beds required for 25 years.
The entire country is divided into 339 areas, with local governments and medical officials discussing it, but many local residents and chiefs remain cautious and the debate is difficult.
The Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare wants to revitalize the discussion by publishing the names of hospitals with poor results.
Comprehensive drill for disaster prevention such as the assumption of Mt.Komagatake eruption, road etc. Wide area with participation of residents, for the first time in 18 years (video): Hokkaido Shimbun
On September 27, a comprehensive disaster prevention drill was held in the forest, Nanae, and Kabe-cho of Toshima-kan.
Approximately 400 people, including staff and residents of 20 institutions including roads and three towns, participated.
It has been held for the first time since the Hokkaido Komagatake Volcano Disaster Prevention Council formulated an evacuation plan incorporating evacuation routes for residents in August.
It has been 18 years since the local residents participated in the extensive training.
At 8:45 a.m., Mt.Komake erupted and the mud flow reached the town at the foot of the mountain.
When the level of volcanic alert was raised to 5 (evacuation), evacuation shelters were opened in Mori and Nanae towns, and residents moved by buses and police cars prepared by each town.
