First Ice at Mt. Norikura (Gifu Shimbun Web) - Yahoo!News
Ice observed for the first time in this season at Tsurugaike Pond in Mt. Norikura Tajodaira = 27th morning, Tanyukawa-cho, Takayama City (provided by Norikura Skyline Management Office)
On the 27th, ice was observed for the first time this season at Tsuruke Pond in Tajodaira (Tanyukawa-cho, Takayama City, Gifu Prefecture, elevation 2702 meters).
Four days later than last year, one day earlier than the average of the past ten years.
According to Norikura Skyline Management Office, around 6:25 a.m., officials patrolling the road confirmed that there were about 2 mm thick ice on the west side of Tsuruke Pond.
The weather was fine and the temperature was 3 degrees.
According to the Gifu Regional Meteorological Observatory, the lowest temperature in the prefecture was 9-5 degrees in Rokumaya, Sokawa-cho, the city.
