The Minister of Health, Labour and Welfare Meets with Leprosy Families Three Provincial Consultations to Eliminate Discrimination | Shizuoka Shimbun
Katsunobu Kato, Minister of Health, Labour and Welfare, announced at a press conference after the cabinet meeting on October 27 that he would meet with families of former leprosy patients on October 2.
They also announced that they would hold consultations with the Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare, Ministry of Education, Culture, Sports, Science and Technology, and Ministry of Justice on the same day to resolve discrimination and prejudice against former patients and their families.
Mr. Kato said, "I would like to listen carefully to the voices of my family and try my best to solve the problem."
In June, the Kumamoto District Court ordered 541 plaintiffs to pay a total of 376 million yen.
Prime Minister Abe Shinzō announced his appeal and confirmed his decision.
The government was also working on compensation measures and human rights awareness.
