Publication of the original manuscript before the suicide of Akutagawa | Shizuoka Shimbun at es
A manuscript written by Ryunosuke Akutagawa, first published in the Tabata Bunshi Village Memorial Hall
The author Ryunosuke AKUTAGAWA (1892-1927) obtained the manuscript of his essay "Shoku Bunshi-mura Memorial Hall" in Kita Ward, Tokyo by 27 days, which he published in his later years, in which he fought literary theory with Junichiro TAZAKI.
It will be exhibited at the museum from October 1.
Although it was known that his essay was included in the whole collection, it was the first time that his manuscript was published publicly.
It is thought that he wrote it a few months before Akutagawa committed suicide, and the memorial researcher, Takeshi Tanei, said, "I can see how Akutagawa, who was debilitating both physically and mentally, faced serious literary challenges with a tragic resolution."
A total of 12 essays were published in the April 27 issue of Bungei Shunju.
Greta Toonbeli: Why do adults laugh and threaten children?
Swedish environmental activist Greta Thunberg gave a speech at the United Nations Climate Action Summit in New York on September 23.
While the speech has attracted attention, it has been reported to insult Greta.
[Tweet Collection] Greta Toonbeli: Why do adults laugh and threaten children?
Political commentators said on American television that Greta was " mentally ill and used by his parents and international left wing," and apologized to the television station.
In Japan, there are many reports online that comment on Greta's comments, such as "I feel sorry for being used" "I should go to school."
On September 26, Greta posted on his Twitter account, "Why do adults spend time laughing and threatening teenagers and children?"
come up with all the lies and conspiracy theories you can think of.
Greta began writing, "You see, it started again, and as you realize, those who hate me are as active as ever, chasing around my appearance, my clothes, my attitude, and where I am different from others, they come up with all the possible lies and conspiracy theories."
The adults pointed out that they did not want to face climate and environmental crises, but they seemed to be distracting from the issue.
To be honest, I don't understand why adults spend time laughing and threatening teenagers and children.
At that time could be another good.
I think they feel threatened by us.
But don't consume your time to pay more attention to them.
The world is starting to wake up.
It is changing.
Even if adults like that change, they don't like it.
See you on the street on Friday!
On Friday 20 the previous week, climate change strikes took place in New York and other parts of the world.
Greta called on him to do it on Friday 27th.
