"I'll kill you" - Yahoo!News
On the 24th of this month, a 33-year-old unemployed man was arrested on a national highway in Kagoshima City, suspected of driving a car relentlessly and threatening to kill a man who was driving.
Katsu Miyahara (33) was arrested for suspicion of intimidation.
According to police, Miyahara is suspected of intimidating a man at the upper intersection where he persistently drove a 24-year-old man on the national highway in Kagoshima City at 0:00 a.m. this month.
On the 25th, a man submitted a report of the damage and the police proceeded to investigate, but on the afternoon of the 26th, a suspect Miyahara went to the police station accompanied by a friend saying, "I was afraid that video of driving on TV and SNS was taken up."
Suspected Miyahara admitted the charge and said that he was forced to brake.
The police are investigating suspected that suspect Miyahara was driving without a license.
