Okayama Art Exchange Opens in the City Center: Sanyo Newspaper Digital | San'Digi
People who go around the classroom in a video work depicting the future 3,000 years later
The international art exhibition "Okayama Art Exchange 2019" held every three years in central Okayama City (hosted by the executive committee of the city, prefecture, etc.) opened on the 27th.
Along with the mysterious title "IF THE SNAKE If Snake," 18 artists from 9 countries enjoy cutting-edge art created by art fans both in Japan and abroad.
This time, the second time following 16 years, we welcomed French artist Pierre Yuig as artistic director, and developed works that utilize Okayama's climate and local resources.
Approximately 40 films and three-dimensional works will be shown at 13 locations including the former Uchiyama Shimoko (Marunouchi, Kita Ward, Okayama City) and the prefectural Tenjinyama Culture Plaza (Otenjin-cho).
Prior to the opening ceremony, a small opening ceremony was held, and about 100 people attended.
Mayor Masao Omori, the chairman of the executive committee, and general producer Yasuharu Ishikawa said, "The works that stimulate intellectual sensibilities and stimulate imagination and creativity are scattered, and it becomes an exhibition that attracts attention from the world."
Families and children studying outside the school visited the school immediately and found a snake-shaped robot that responds to the sounds of the surrounding area in the dohyo of the school yard.
I enjoyed the art that led to different worlds.
While traveling with my father, a first-year high school student in Tokyo (15) said, "It's interesting to make use of the atmosphere of the old school building, and I can imagine the time that flows into this place."
It is closed on November 24 (the following day if it is a national holiday).
Hong Kong rally in five years of the rain umbrella movement tens of thousands, aiming for a general election | Shizuoka Shimbun at Es
Five years have passed since the "Ambrella Movement" started, and people gathered at the meeting venue = 28th Hong Kong (co-operation)
[Collaboration with Hong Kong] On the 28th of May, 2014, a large-scale demonstration called the "Ambrella Movement," which sought democratization of the election of the Hong Kong Executive Director, was held in a park near the Hong Kong Government Headquarters building of the Admiralty, which had the largest base of the demonstration party.
Some young people occupied the main road around the venue and threw a bottle of fire into the government building.
As protests started with the amendment of the Fugitive Ordinance continued, the participants renewed their determination to fight until the realization of a "true ordinary election" that could not be won at the time.
The protest, which began in earnest in June, took 112 days, more than 79 days after the Umbrella Movement, and the demands of the demonstrators expanded to "five major demands" such as electoral reform.
Ibaraki Kokutai Opens today 28th|Saga Shimbun News|Saga Shimbun
The 74th National Sports Festival "Ikiiki Ibaraki Yume Kokutai 2019" was held on 28th, and the general opening ceremony was held at Kasamatsu Sports Park Athletic Stadium in Hitachinaka City, Ibaraki Prefecture.
Approximately 400 players and coaches from Saga Prefecture will compete in 33 competitions, excluding those held before the exhibition.
The prefecture ranked 43rd for three consecutive years until last year, but rose to 33rd last year.
This year, we aim to reach the first half of the 20th place.
In the pre-season competition held by the 16th, the Saga Women's High School of rhythmic gymnastics boys and girls, as well as the adult girls and boys' girls of gymnastics, all finished sixth.
I want to advance to the top of each competition by riding the flow.
At the general opening ceremony, 83 athletes, directors, and officers of the headquarters of the prefectural government marched on the 40th entrance, and a rugby boy, Kugo Ishikawa (Saga Koko), was the flag bearer.
On the first day, wrestling, table tennis and karate are held.
